# Book Order Line

A Book Order Line is the request, within a Book Order, for a specific number of copies of a selected Medium.
This may also be referred to as a "Book Order Details" in some organizations.

◇

attributes:

    quantity:
        name: "quantity"
        details: The number of copies of the selected Medium being requested.
        rules: 1 .. unconstrained, to the whole number

    price:
        name: "price per copy"
        details: |
            The price of the selected Medium when it was added to this Book Order.
            This is how much the customer will be/was charaged when the
            Book Order is/was paid for. This allows WebBooks to change the price of Media
            yet still be able to correctly calculate order-level profit. Sometimes,
            Media may be offered for free.
        rules: $0.00 .. unconstrained in US Dollars, to the whole cent

    state:
        name: "state"
        details: Shows the business processing status of this Book Order Line.
        rules: enumeration of the states in the state model

    is_packable:
        name: "is packable?"
        details: Shows if this Book Order Line is currently packable or not.
        derivation: |
            Always true if this line refers to eBook medium.
            If this line refers to print medium, true only when .quantity <= Print Medium .stock level

    sales:
        name: "sales?"
        details: Shows the total dollar amount of this Book Order Line.
        derivation: .quantity * .price per copy

    profit:
        name: "profit?"
        details: Shows the amount of profit generated by this Book Order Line.
        derivation: .quantity * (.price per copy - Medium.acquisition cost) via For

    user_keys:
        name: "user keys?"
        details: Shows the user key a Custoemr needs to unlock an eBook on their reader.
        derivation: when linked to eBook medium then eBook.Medium.user key? via For, otherwise nothing.

states:

  Open:
    details: The book order line is created.

  Placed:
    details: A physical medium book is ready for packing.

  Completed:
    details: The book order line is shipped, or handed off to customer as eBook.


events:

    "«new»":
        details: Create this Book Order Line.
        parameters:
            - name: book order
              source: somewhere
            - name: medium
              source: somewhere
            - name: quantity
              source: somewhere

    "«destroy»":
        details: Remove this book order line.

    Place:
        details: Purchase the the Book Order Line.

    Packed:
        details: The Book Order Line is ready to ship.

    Completed:
        details: No more work needed on this Book Order Line.


guards:

    EBookMedium:
        details: "eBook medium"

    PrintMedium:
        details: "print medium"

actions:

    Initialize:
        details: Start a new Book Order Line.
        requires:
            - qty in reange of .quantity
        guarantees:
            - |
                one new Book Order Line exists with:
                    .quanity == qty,
                    .price per copy == Medium.selling price,
                    this line is linked to its Book Order and Medium

    MarkAsPacked:
        details: physical medium is all packed for shipping
        guarantees:
            - if linked to Print Medium then picked(.quantity) has been signaled for it

transitions:

    - {from: "", event: "«new»", to: "Open", action: "Initialize"}

    - {from: "Open", event: "«destroy»", to: ""}
    - {from: "Open", event: "Place", to: "Placed", guard: "PrintMedium"}
    - {from: "Open", event: "Place", to: "Completed", guard: "EBookMedium"}

    - {from: "Placed", event: "Packed", to: "Completed", action: "MarkAsPacked"}


